{"id":863,"date":"2009-06-25T08:36:12","date_gmt":"2009-06-25T13:36:12","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/words_periods_arial_company_na.php"},"modified":"2009-06-25T08:36:12","modified_gmt":"2009-06-25T13:36:12","slug":"words_periods_arial_company_na","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/words_periods_arial_company_na.php","title":{"rendered":"Words. Periods. Arial. Company Name."},"content":{"rendered":"<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/namics_logo.gif\" alt=\"Namics Logo, Before and After\" \/><\/p>\n<p>The background on this will be brief as I lack in German fluency. <a href=\"http:\/\/www.namics.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Namics<\/a> is a web design and development, and information technology company based in Frankfurt, Germany and from what our generous tipster informs us it is one of the biggest in Europe. They recently launched a new identity, designed by Zurich based firm <a href=\"http:\/\/www.heads.ch\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Heads<\/a>, that replaces their ambiguous icon for an ever-changing wordmark.<\/p><!--more--><p>Labeled by Head as &#8220;the world&#8217;s first &#8216;Real Time Corporate Identity&#8217;,&#8221; the Namics logo is a constantly fluctuating identity based on words preceding the Namics name, that are input by its employees through any number of methods, be it Twitter or SMS. The effect is, of course, best appreciated on the web site, where the logo restarts itself over and over with a new group of words. But if you look at <a href=\"http:\/\/www.heads.ch\/index.php?content=referenzen&#038;lang=en#82-Dynamic-Branding--Namics\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">the project page on Head&#8217;s web site<\/a>, you can see that the result feels as dynamic in print as it does online.<\/p>\n<p>The best part is that the identity is set in&hellip; Arial. <\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/namics_01.gif\" alt=\"Namics Logo, System\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/namics_02.gif\" alt=\"Namics Logo, System\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/namics_03.jpg\" alt=\"Namics Logo, System\" \/><\/p>\n<p><span class=\"small\"><strong>Thanks to <a href=\"http:\/\/WWW.TWITTER.COM\/ADRIAN_N\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Adrian Nussbaum<\/a> for the tip.<\/strong><\/span><\/p>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/images\/excerpt_empty.gif\" alt=\"Excerpt Empty\" \/>","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"episode_type":"","audio_file":"","duration":"","filesize":"","date_recorded":"","explicit":"","block":"","filesize_raw":""},"categories":[9,26,88],"tags":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/863"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=863"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/863\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=863"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=863"},{"taxonomy":"post